                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The yeth hound emits an unearthly howl audible up to 300 feet away. Any non-fiend creature that hears the howl must succeed at a <span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-traits=\"auditory,concentrate,divine,enchantment,fear,mental,fiend\" data-pf2-label=\"Bay DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Will</span> save or become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 1}. Any creature that critically fails and is within 60 feet of the yeth hound is instead @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 3} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fleeing]{Fleeing} for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds} (or until it recovers from its frightened condition).</p>\n<p>Whether it succeeds or fails the saving throw, the creature is then temporarily immune to Bay for 24 hours.</p>"
